  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/monad.foundation/f047dfbe-9ef4-4132-9939-e0f3e9faa154/application",
    "company": "Monad Foundation",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "bb07a2876e1b58df",
    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "The Monad Foundation is a team of dedicated ecosystem and community builders who are on a mission to massively grow the impact of decentralized tech. We believe that the Monad https://monad.xyz/ blockchain--the performant and parallel EVM Layer 1--will help decentralized apps eat the world.\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nMonad Foundation is looking for someone to join us in Workplace Operations to own the day-to-day experience of our NYC office and support key moments across the employee lifecycle. This person ensures our physical workplace runs smoothly, our team feels supported, and in-office logistics are seamless for employees, candidates, and visitors alike.\n\nYou’ll partner closely with Recruiting, IT, and the broader Operations team, serving as a central connector across workplace logistics, employee experience, and office coordination. This role requires strong communication and organizational skills, along with a natural “host mentality” - you are often the person who makes things feel thoughtful, smooth, and well taken care of. We’re looking for someone highly proactive and detail-oriented who thrives in a fast-paced, evolving environment and can confidently manage multiple workstreams simultaneously.\n\nThe office is in Flatiron, Manhattan, NYC. This is for an on-site (5 days/week in office) role.\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\n - Resourceful, self-motivated, and comfortable taking ownership\n\n - A strong communicator who collaborates well across teams and functions\n\n - Adaptable and calm in a dynamic, startup-style environment\n\n - Highly organized with sharp attention to detail\n   \n\n - A natural “host” - you enjoy making people feel welcome and supported in a shared space\n\n - Brings a positive, solutions-oriented mindset and approaches challenges with a proactive, can-do attitude\n\n - Comfortable with dogs (we have an office dog!)\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\n - 3+ years of experience in workplace operations, office management, employee experience, or similar operational roles\n\n - Proficient in workplace tools such as Google Workspace, Slack, and Notion\n\n - Strong time management skills with the ability to independently manage multiple priorities\n\n - Comfortable working on-site and handling in-person logistics daily\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including experience working with both internal teams and external vendors\n\n - Based in NYC and able to work from the office 5 days per week\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\nYou’ll own aspects of the day-to-day experience and operations of our NYC workplace, while also supporting cross-departmental initiatives that enhance how our global team works together.\n\n\nOFFICE \u0026 VENDOR OPERATIONS\n\nHelp maintain a functional, well-run office environment through vendor coordination and workplace logistics.\n\n - Serve as the primary point of contact for office vendors, including cleaning services and maintenance providers\n\n - Coordinate ad hoc office repairs and facilities-related needs\n\n - Manage office supply, kitchen, and amenities ordering to keep the workplace stocked and functional\n\n - Support general workplace logistics to ensure a smooth and comfortable office environment\n\n\nWORKPLACE EXPERIENCE \u0026 EMPLOYEE SUPPORT\n\nSupport a thoughtful and well-run in-office experience for employees.\n\n - Coordinate in-office employee visits, including desk assignments and access setup\n\n - Maintain the NYC office and workplace operations calendars and support general workplace and internal ops team documentation\n\n - Help manage culture and appreciation moments, including birthday gifts and small team experiences\n\n - Coordinate recurring in-office experiences such as monthly team lunches and other employee-focused moments\n\n - Assist with occasional outbound shipments and other in-office logistics\n   \n\n\nRECRUITING \u0026 CANDIDATE EXPERIENCE\n\nPartner with Recruiting to help create a seamless and welcoming in-person candidate experience.\n\n - Support logistics for on-site interviews\n\n - Welcome candidates to the office and help ensure a professional, friendly, and well-organized interview day\n   \n\n\nCROSS-FUNCTIONAL SUPPORT\n\nWork closely with internal teams to ensure the office is ready for both everyday work and special initiatives.\n\n - Collaborate with IT on conference room and in-office technology readiness (IT owns systems; you help ensure spaces are prepared and usable)\n\n - Partner with the broader Operations and leadership team to continuously improve employee experience and company operations\n\n - Support the Ecosystem team with logistics for in-office events\n\n\nSALARY AND BENEFITS\n\nMinimum full-time salary of $120,000 (**This is not a guarantee of compensation or salary; a final offer amount may vary based on factors including, but not limited to, experience, domain expertise, and geographic location). Benefits for full-time employees may include medical, dental, and vision insurance (100% coverage for employees), paid time off, paid parental leave, and 11 company-observed holidays.\n\n\nWHY WORK WITH US\n\n - Challenging problems. You’ll work on extremely challenging problems with massive impact.\n\n - Huge opportunity. The Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) standard is ubiquitous, but existing EVM-compatible chains are slow and bandwidth-constrained. Monad’s core innovations offer developers the best of both worlds (portability and performance) and are a game-changer for mass user adoption in crypto.\n\n - The right team. You’ll be part of an exceptional and highly-motivated team\n\n - Culture. We’re a lean team working together to achieve very ambitious goals. We are united in our culture of collaboration, low ego, and high-quality output. As an early member of our team, you’ll help continue to shape our culture.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
